President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring March 15, 2020, as a National Day of Prayer for all Americans affected by the coronavirus pandemic. In the proclamation, he encourages Americans of all faiths to pray for those who have been impacted by the virus, including those who have suffered harm or lost loved ones. He asks for prayers for the health and well-being of fellow Americans and for God's healing hand to be placed upon the nation. The President also calls for prayers for the medical professionals, first responders, and leaders working to combat the virus. He emphasizes the importance of prayer and unity in overcoming this challenge and expresses confidence in God's ability to help the country endure.